---
import PageFrame from '../components/PageFrame.astro';
import { ci2Page, ciComponents, ciFirsts } from '../data/site';
---

<PageFrame title={ci2Page.title} description={ci2Page.metaDescription} currentPath="/ci2" ctaHref="/contact" ctaLabel="Talk about CI²">
  <section class="hero" style="text-align:center;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" data-reveal>The Operating System</div>
      <div class="formula formula--large" data-reveal>(AI<sup>2</sup>)<span class="plus">+</span>(HI<sup>2</sup>)<span class="equals">=</span>(CI<sup>2</sup>)</div>
      <p class="hero__sub" data-reveal style="margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">Collaborative Intelligence™ is the operating philosophy of WORK LABS. Not AI consulting. Not nostalgia for human craft. A disciplined way to combine speed, judgment, possibility, and taste.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container split">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow" data-reveal>The Thesis</div>
        <h1 class="page-title" data-reveal>The future is not artificial.<br /><span class="italic muted">It is collaborative.</span></h1>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="lede" data-reveal>AI can generate almost anything. That does not make everything worth choosing. The scarce resource is still direction: knowing what matters, what to remove, what to protect, and what a brand should mean.</p>
        <p class="lede" data-reveal>CI² names the third intelligence that appears when artificial intelligence and human intelligence are working together in the right relationship.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split split--end">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" data-reveal>The Geometry</div>
          <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal>Three intelligences.<br /><span class="italic muted">One system.</span></h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede" data-reveal>Each component is squared. Each component is required. The third, the one that matters, emerges when the first two operate in collaboration, not opposition.</p>
      </div>
      <svg class="triangle" data-reveal viewBox="0 0 380 280" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
        <line class="tri-line" style="--d:0ms;" pathLength="1" x1="60" y1="220" x2="320" y2="220" stroke="#f5f3ee" stroke-width="1" />
        <line class="tri-line" style="--d:160ms;" pathLength="1" x1="60" y1="220" x2="60" y2="60" stroke="#f5f3ee" stroke-width="1" />
        <line class="tri-line" style="--d:320ms;" pathLength="1" x1="60" y1="60" x2="320" y2="220" stroke="#c6a35a" stroke-width="2.5" />
        <circle cx="60" cy="220" r="5" fill="#c6a35a" />
        <circle cx="60" cy="60" r="5" fill="#c6a35a" />
        <circle cx="320" cy="220" r="5" fill="#c6a35a" />
        <text x="36" y="148" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="22" fill="#f5f3ee" text-anchor="end">HI</text>
        <text x="190" y="252" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="22" fill="#f5f3ee" text-anchor="middle">AI</text>
        <text x="210" y="124" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="22" fill="#c6a35a" text-anchor="middle">CI</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" data-reveal>The Components</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal>Where each intelligence belongs.</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid" style="margin-top:70px;">
        {ciComponents.map((component) => (
          <article class="card" data-reveal>
            <div class="card__number">{component.label}</div>
            <h3 class="card-title">{component.title}</h3>
            <p>{component.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--dark">
    <div class="container split split--end">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow" data-reveal>Commercial Logic</div>
        <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal>CI² makes the work faster without making it shallower.</h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="lede" data-reveal>Inside WORK LABS, CI² is not a slogan. It is the operating layer beneath brand strategy, consulting, identity, packaging, and the Foundry. It creates more options, then applies better judgment.</p>
        <div class="cards-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr; margin-top:38px;">
          {['More informed creative development.', 'Sharper strategic sequencing.', 'Better prepared brand platforms and decisions.'].map((item) => (
            <article class="card" data-reveal><p>{item}</p></article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" data-reveal>Pattern Recognition</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal>This is not the first time WORK LABS has named what was coming.</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid" style="margin-top:70px;">
        {ciFirsts.map((item) => (
          <article class="card" data-reveal>
            <div class="card__number">{item.year}</div>
            <h3 class="card-title">{item.title}</h3>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--dark" style="text-align:center;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" data-reveal>The Point</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal style="margin-inline:auto;">The advantage is not having the machine.<br /><span class="italic muted">It is knowing what to ask of it.</span></h2>
      <div class="hero__actions" data-reveal style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/consulting">Apply CI²</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/brand-foundry">See the Foundry</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageFrame>
